pEquity dividend income (1%-3%) generated by ensuring that dividend payments are sustainable and expected to grow over time.  This is complemented by targeting companies with policies that return cash to shareholders via share repurchases.Equity option income (3%-5%) contribute to returns by using conservative option strategies that generate additional incomeCurrencies, commodities, and index trades (~5%+) produce returns for the portfolio by capitalizing on macro-economic trendsPortfolio protection minimize losses in a declining market enviornmentReal Estate Private EquityInvestment StrategyInvestment CircumstancesOpportunistic value-add properties in niche sectors that exhibit strong demographic trends and historical resistance to economic downturns.Substantially less competition from large real estate private equity funds and institutions.Abundance of fragmented sectors and geographic markets.New supply in virtually every real estate sector remains near record lows.Investment CharacteristicsAssets trading below replacement cost.Value-add opportunities where operational improvements can be implemented in order increase cash flows. Assets in markets with barriers to entry.Geographic regions undergoing long term positive secular economic growth trends.Equity investment up to $7 million.Target SectorsMulti-family Triple-net lease retail Flex space/industrial Medical office Off-campus student housing Current Real Estate PortfolioShadow Tree ApartmentsDenver,CO118 UnitsAmherst ApartmentsDenver, CO81 UnitsFitzsimons Place ApartmentsDenver, CO99 UnitsElm Grove ApartmentsDenver, CO59 UnitsVillages at WoodmenColorado Springs, CO183 UnitsWind River Place AparmentsColorado Springs, CO120 UnitsResidence at Austin BluffsColorado Springs, CO312 UnitsChestnut SpringsColorado Springs, CO92 UnitsSteel Bridge OfficesDenver, CO24,000 SQF Office Building/Parking LotHuron Street CondoDenver, CO144 UnitsE. Silverado & BermudaLas Vegas, NV33,000 Rentable SQFRainbow and MardonLas Vegas, 